Text.Value: But who knows? Maybe the old man's tastes've changed since I left.
You taught me how. And then you destroyed me.
There's no escape. No escape for us and no escape for you, Astarion!
We'll find a way.

EditorData.stateContext: Sebastian/Prisoner is on his knees, head bowed

Text.Value: They're my conquests. I pursued them, seduced them, then brought them to Cazador. He told us he was feeding on them.
Astarion - do you know who these prisoners are?
Free? We'll never be free while that monster lives.
Stop whining - the only thing that matters is killing Cazador. He's responsible for all of this.
How did they get here? What is Cazador doing with them? I should have guessed there was more to it than Raphael would ever have told.
How long have I been down here?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Getting from his knees to his feet

Text.Value: Free from this nightmare? It doesn't feel possible...
This nightmare never ends and it's your fault. You did this, damn you!

EditorData.NodeContext: Accusing Astarion, a mix of rage of despair

Text.Value: If I had to guess, I'd say they're part of his ritual. But where in the hells did they come from?
Sebastian.

EditorData.NodeContext: says his name in shock, quietly

Text.Value: What do you want to happen?
You remember me.
So Cazador marked them too - bound us all to his ritual.
The grand chamber, just ahead...
Kill him? That monster?
You took them from me. You took everything from me!
Gods - these poor people.
Look at the symbols - they all have scars.
You don't understand - it's not just him.
RAGH!

EditorData.AnimationTags: [AL] Full custom animation needed for the prisoner. Astarion can use a construction
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Prisoner launches himself forward, smashing against the bars, reaching for Astarion, who steps back just in time. The prisoner collapses sobbing.
EditorData.SFXTags: sound of body hitting solid metal bars

Text.Value: It can't be -

EditorData.AnimationTags: [AL] This will be the _OUT of the previous custom animation

Text.Value: Is this how you used to live, Astarion?
What?
You can't stop him. No one can stop him.
It's not just him - I know so many of these faces.
You can't. It's not possible...
You. I know you.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Prisoner at the back of the cell, in the shadows

Text.Value: They could be sacrifices for the Black Mass, but where did he get them all?
We'll set you free - what else?
Is this how all of your lovers end up?
Help? From the one who cursed us to this?!
That depends on you. Can you control your hunger?
I know so many of these faces.
Sit tight - we'll be back.
Don't. Not now.
I have no idea what these wretches are doing here. 'The Master' had a more refined palate than this.
We'll set you free.
No - no, you can't leave us here. Not now - not like this!
Leave.
Hardly. Cazador didn't keep me in luxury, but I've never seen anything like this.
*Approaching the cells, you're met by hollow-eyed faces. There's an almost physical stink of decay and neglect.*

EditorData.AnimationTags: [AL] Use construction for idling characters. New poses can be made from already existing animations
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: shot of the prisoners in the cells

Text.Value: Where is he now?
I know these faces - every one that shares my scar.
Let Astarion answer.
I don't even know what this prison is. He hid all of this from me and the others.
But even if you can kill him - what then? What happens to us?
We need to go. Now.
You were handsome. Shy. You'd never been kissed.
But he turned them to spawn. He turned every last one so he'd have souls for this cursed ritual.
Then they're bound to the Black Mass too. Bound through the scars. And through me.
How long?
His staff. It controls everything.
My family - my friends - they're gone...

EditorData.NodeContext: cracked voice, his mind is slipping

Text.Value: I damn you to the Hells! I damn you to misery! I damn you - damn you...

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Breaking down, crying, falling to his knees
EditorData.NodeContext: Mix of rage and sobbing tears - Sebastian is broken

Text.Value: Whatever this is, we don't have time for it.
Oh they're disgusting. Cazador never fed on wretches like this.
Whatever you do, just do it quickly. I can't go on waiting...
On second thought, freeing a bunch of ravenous spawn seems like a bad idea.
Trust me when I say I know the feeling. But you can resist the urge.
We'll be back. You have my word.
Where's the key to your cell?
And then? What happens to us?
You - no. You're dead.

EditorData.NodeContext: looking at a victim of his he thought was long dead

Text.Value: His scar matches one of the runes on your back.
But he never sets it down - you'll never get it.
I don't know. I just don't want to die down here. Please...
His staff. It controls everything.
*Beneath the dirt and blood, you notice that every prisoner has a rune carved into their flesh.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Close up of main prisoner's face, and the rune-scar on his cheek

Text.Value: Help? Help? There's no helping us while that monster lives.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Astarion frowns and approaches the cell to get a better look at the prisoner who spoke in the previous node. The prisoner steps out of the shadow - he's emaciated, filthy, and dressed in rags that were once finery

Text.Value: That's why we're here - to destroy Cazador.
How did they get here? What is Cazador doing with them? My brethren spoke nothing of this...
You called me so many sweet things. My name sounded like a lyric on your tongue.

EditorData.NodeContext: sad but not too emotional - this character is traumatised - addressing Astarion from inside a cell (Astarion is standing outside the cell looking in)

Text.Value: I'm just surprised to see such wretched-looking specimens - Cazador had a more refined palate than this.
I - I don't know. It's all I've ever felt...
I have no intention of freeing a bunch of ravenous spawn.
Who is he?
One hundred and seventy years. You were one of my first.

EditorData.NodeContext: muted, with a touch of shame

Text.Value: I promise you, I know that feeling all too well. But it can be done.
Like I said - we'll set you free.
Free? I'll never be free. I can't even die!
Cazador plans to use you in his ritual - that's why he scarred you. Let us help.
You're the one from the tavern. You smiled and joked and got me drunk.

EditorData.NodeContext: sad but not too emotional - this character is traumatised - addressing Astarion from inside a cell (Astarion is standing outside the cell looking in)

Text.Value: Gods, I know so many of these faces.
I don't blame that monster. I blame him.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: pointing at Astarion and snarling in anger

Synopsis: COM dialog with the prisoners in Cazador's Palace. Astarion meets Sebastian - a young man he seduced and brought to Cazador - for the first time in 170 years. Astarion was sure Sebastian was dead, but Cazador secretly turned him into a vampire spawn. If you aggrevate Sebastian, he'll be so full of hate and pain that he'll curse you.
